
// This Hyperlambda code sets the value of the [.connection] node by concatenating strings to create a connection string. It uses [strings.concat] to combine a static string "[generic|" with the value of the [database] node from [.arguments], and ends with a closing bracket "]". The [set-value] slot assigns this concatenated result to [.connection].
set-value:x:@.connection
   strings.concat
      .:[generic|
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/database
      .:]
